President Barack Obama issued a statement on the 70th anniversary of the attack on Pearl Harbor, honoring the memory of the more than 2,400 American patriots who lost their lives. He expressed gratitude to the veterans and survivors of Pearl Harbor who fought back heroically and inspired the nation. Obama highlighted their role in defeating fascism and building a strong economy in post-war America. He emphasized the importance of standing together as Americans and reaffirmed the commitment to keeping the country strong, free, and prosperous. Additionally, he pledged to take care of the troops, veterans, and military families as they have taken care of the nation.